main event: An unidentified flying object was sighted on July 16, 1965, in Presto, Pennsylvania.
interesting points: The object appeared oval and multi-colored, predominantly green, with antenna-like protrusions., It flew at a very low altitude of 50 to 100 feet and moved in a straight line too slow to be an aircraft., The sighting lasted approximately five minutes and the object disappeared instantaneously., The report concluded that data was very poor, and it was regarded as an aircraft sighting., No physical evidence or photographs were collected during this sighting.
witness description: Witnesses are not specified in the report.
